node.text:
S'MORE, whoever invented the word was definitely onto something because it is truly impossible to have just one of these warm, gooey, chocolatey treats (believe me I've tried).
I found a workaround though, by caking a giant version! Technically it’s only one s’more. Am I a genius? Yes, yes I am.

node.text:
If there was ever a cake to get you chocolate wasted, it would be this one right here. My Nutella Mega Cake is a combination of chocolate cake layers, hazelnut meringues, nutella buttercream, Ferrero Rochers and an ENTIRE jar of Nutella. Did I go a bit overboard with the chocolate decorations? Never! The limit does not exist! 

P.s. You can find all the recipes used in this cake in my FREE Basics of Baking Program. Because we all deserve to get a little chocolate wasted once and a while 😉

Sushi? Pizza? Indian? Drive Thru? When it comes to takeout it's always SO hard to make a decision in my house. We can never agree what to get which is why I went ahead and caked all of my favorite takeout foods. 
 
Don't worry guys I've got dinner AND dessert covered tonight! 

Shoutout to @hellthyjunkfood for the hilarious Wendy's Frosty Collab 😂

node.text:
One of the best flavor combos out there imo because if you know me you'll know of my love for banana cake. This mega masterpiece is stacked with luscious Italian Meringue Buttercream, caramelized bananas, dulce de leche and toffee candies then coated with banana and plantain chips. Have I convinced you to make it yet? 😉

You can find the full recipe here https://howtocakeit.com/blogs/recipes/banoffee-mega-cake

node.text:
The infamous Pencil Cake...if you've been around since it's creation you already know my love-hate relationship with this cake. I never imagined that I’d make a mistake caking one of my favourite things! But...I got a little too excited and accidentally created an eight-sided pencil instead of the standard six sides 🤦🏽‍♀️.

Yup. Still not over it.

Lunch box? Check ✔️
Juice box? Check ✔️

Massive PB&J Sandwich? Check ✔️
Cake? CHECK 😁👌🏽

It might be a little early to start packing school lunch boxes but it's never too soon to seek out cakespiration! 

Hands up if you'd try making one of these cakes to celebrate back to school with your kids 🙋🏽‍♀️ .

node.text:
As some of you might have guessed by now, I really really love cake 😏. While I typically use fondant in a lot of mine, most of our online Bake You Happy Tutorials don't, which is why I wanted to show off some of these gorgeous cakes from our talented artists 🙌🏽. We've got a decadent S'mores Cake, dreamy Boho Macrame cake and stunning Sculpted Buttercream Sheet Cake with NO fondant required! 
If you'd like to sign up for any of these caketastic classes head to my link in bio!

node.text: I think it goes without saying but when it comes to cake I'm definitely in the camp of "the bigger the better"😋. That's why I'm always caking up giant versions of things! Here are a few of my favorite jumbo cakes that I've made over the years (minus the disastrous McDonalds Apple Pie Cake maybe, because if you know you know 🤬)

node.text:
Soo who else is still drooling at the thought of my peanut butter cake? 🤤You guys have to try it out - it's a game-changer for all those peanut butter lovers out there (I def recommend trying it with chocolate chips)!

You can find this recipe along with tons more in my FREE Basics of Baking Course which I created to help give you the building blocks for creating beautiful cakes. 

Link here 👉 https://bit.ly/basicsofbaking or head to my bio 😊

node.text:
What do astronauts and aliens have in common? I wish I had a better punchline, but it's actually that they both taste (and look) absolutely delicious in cookie form!

Jareds upcoming Outer Space Cookie tutorial which is perfect for an intermediate cookier looking to advance their skills. 

Sound like you? Sign up at the link in my bio!

S'MORE, whoever invented the word was definitely onto something because it is truly impossible to have just one of these warm, gooey, chocolatey treats (believe me I've tried).
I found a workaround though, by caking a giant version! Technically it’s only one s’more. Am I a genius? Yes, yes I am.

You can snag the full recipe in my FREE basics of baking course where I give you the low down on how to nail this recipe every time!

node.text:
If there was ever a cake to get you chocolate wasted, it would be this one right here. My Nutella Mega Cake is a combination of chocolate cake layers, hazelnut meringues, nutella buttercream, Ferrero Rochers and an ENTIRE jar of Nutella. Did I go a bit overboard with the chocolate decorations? Never! The limit does not exist! 

P.s. You can find all the recipes used in this cake in my FREE Basics of Baking Program. Because we all deserve to get a little chocolate wasted once and a while 😉

You've been asking for a fondant class...and I obviously agree 😉.

This brand new fondant 101 class with @eatcakebemerry is the perfect starting point to begin your fondant journey, imperfections and decorators of all skill levels welcome!

You can sign up by visiting the link in @howtocakeit’s bio.

You know you want a bite too 😉

That's a Goat Cheese, Roasted Garlic and Caramelized Fig Galette in case you were wondering and yes, I went back for a second slice. Obviously. This heavenly Fall morsel comes from this month's Bakebook, Baked. I'll be eating my way through Suzie's recipes, chatting and baking with her for the rest of September and would love for you to join us.

Sign up for the Bakebook Club at the link in my bio!

node.text:
Sushi? Pizza? Indian? Drive Thru? When it comes to takeout it's always SO hard to make a decision in my house. We can never agree what to get which is why I went ahead and caked all of my favorite takeout foods. 
 
Don't worry guys I've got dinner AND dessert covered tonight! 

Shoutout to @hellthyjunkfood for the hilarious Wendy's Frosty Collab 😂

node.text:
We all have that one treat that reminds us instantly of summer. For me it's these iconic tri-colored popsicles and trying to guess the flavor of each layer without looking at the box (but seriously what even is blue raspberry??) 
What's your favorite nostalgic summer treat?

node.text:
Give me a break, give me a break, break me off a piece of that Kit Kat CAKE!

I don’t play favorites when it comes to my cakes, but if I did this KitKat Mega Cake would be in my top 5 for sure. It used three flavors of cake to complement the three specialty KitKats I found: Have Your Cake, Good Fortune Green Tea and Totally Butter Tart!

Swipe to see how I brought this mega masterpiece to life and let me know down below which KitKats YOU would choose to make your cake!

node.text:
One of the best flavor combos out there imo because if you know me you'll know of my love for banana cake. This mega masterpiece is stacked with luscious Italian Meringue Buttercream, caramelized bananas, dulce de leche and toffee candies then coated with banana and plantain chips. Have I convinced you to make it yet? 😉

You can find the full recipe here https://howtocakeit.com/blogs/recipes/banoffee-mega-cake
